   FRIENDS OF THE LIBRARY
   [bottom.gif]

   [audiobookstext.gif] [backbutton.gif]
   Literary fare for all ages can be found in audio versions in our AV
   department.  Expert orators, guest celebrities, and even the authors
   themselves narrate unabridged versions of renowned books (some abridged
   titles are available).

   To see recent additions to our downtown location's audiobook
   collection, click on any of the following audiobook category links,
   featuring:
     * favorite children's titles
     * popular works for teens
     * the best in adult mystery, science fiction, fiction and non-fiction

   For loan limits and loan period information, click here.

   MP3 PLAYERS ARE HERE!  Kalamazoo Public Library has become the first
   public library in the U. S. to loan digital audio books.  Ttiles are
   being purchased from Audible.com, the leading provider of downloadable
   spoken word audio.   Audible.com offers a vast selection of
   audiobooks.  For more information about this service (including KPL's
   first and second quarter evaluations of it), click here.

   Learn more about the evolving world of spoken word audio by navigating
   the following website:

   www.audiopub.org



